Privacy Policy
Chess Elo Guesser
Last updated: April 8, 2026

This Privacy Policy describes how Chess Elo Guesser (“the App,” “we,” “us,” or “our”) handles information when you use our mobile application (including builds distributed through app stores), any related website or GitHub Pages content, and connected online features such as leaderboards. By using the App, you agree to this Privacy Policy.

1. Who we are
"Chess Elo Guesser is operated by an independent publisher based in Turkey. For privacy requests, contact us at kuponai.app@gmail.com."

2. Information we collect
Depending on how you use the App, we may process the following categories of information:

Leaderboard and nickname data. If you choose to register a public nickname, we store that nickname together with a pseudonymous device identifier we assign on your device, game mode, scores, and related session metadata. This is used to display rankings and to enforce fair-use rules (for example, rate limiting). We do not require a password or email for basic play with a nickname; your nickname is not verified as uniquely “yours” beyond our technical rules.
Locally stored identifiers and preferences. The App may save a random player identifier, nickname, accessibility or audio preferences (such as music mute and volume), and similar settings on your device using local storage or equivalent APIs.
Gameplay and technical data. When you interact with our backend (for example, Supabase or similar services), standard technical data may be processed automatically, such as timestamps, IP addresses, device/browser characteristics as observed by the service, and request metadata needed for security, abuse prevention, and reliability.
Third-party content. The App may load chess games or related metadata from datasets or services you configure. It may also load fonts, libraries, or media from third-party hosts (for example, standard sound assets as referenced in the App configuration). Those providers may collect data under their own policies and HTTP logs.
We do not intentionally collect precise real-time location. We do not require you to provide your government name, postal address, or phone number to play.

3. How we use information
We use the information described above to:

Operate the game, including loading positions and validating guesses;
Provide leaderboards, daily challenges, and related competitive features;
Maintain security, detect abuse, and enforce technical rate limits;
Improve stability and fix bugs;
Comply with applicable law where required.
We do not sell your personal information. We do not use your data to show behavioural advertising through third-party ad networks as part of this App’s core design; if that ever changes, we will update this policy.

4. Legal bases (EEA, UK, and similar regions)
If data protection laws in your region require a “legal basis,” we rely on: (a) performance of a contract / steps you request (running the App and features you activate); (b) our legitimate interests in operating, securing, and improving the service, provided those interests are not overridden by your rights; and (c) compliance with legal obligations where applicable. Where consent is required for optional processing, we will ask separately.

5. Sharing and processors
We use infrastructure and software providers to host backend services (for example, database and API providers). Those providers process data on our behalf under contractual safeguards appropriate to the service. We may also disclose information if required by law, court order, or to protect the rights, safety, or integrity of users and the public.

6. Data retention
We retain leaderboard-related records for as long as needed to operate the feature and as required by law. You may be able to delete certain stored information through in-app controls (for example, an account or nickname deletion flow where offered). Residual backups may persist for a limited period in ordinary course. Local data on your device remains until you clear app data or uninstall the App.

7. Children’s privacy
The App is not directed at children under 13 (or the minimum age required in your jurisdiction). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children in a targeted manner. If you believe we have collected such information, contact us and we will take reasonable steps to delete it.

8. International transfers
Our service providers may process data in countries other than your own. Where required, we rely on appropriate transfer mechanisms recognised by applicable law (such as standard contractual clauses) or other lawful bases.

9. Your rights
Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or restrict processing of your personal data, to object to certain processing, to data portability, or to withdraw consent where processing is consent-based. You may also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority. To exercise rights, contact us using the details below.

10. Security
We implement reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect information. No method of transmission or storage is completely secure; we cannot guarantee absolute security.

11. Changes
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will post the updated version on this page and revise the “Last updated” date. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy where permitted by law.

12. Contact
For privacy questions or requests, contact: kuponai.app@gmail.com
